2009-03-07  Manuel Pégourié-Gonnard <mpg@elzevir.fr>

	* texdoc.tlu:
	- BugFix: some options (-v, -V, --verbosity) didn't match the help
	message.

2009-02-08  Manuel Pégourié-Gonnard <mpg@elzevir.fr>

	* texdoc.tlu: 
	- Display the svn rev if version ends with '+'. Display version more
	often (-h, -f).
	- Add a new level of config file and the new config option
	'lastfile_switch', allowing to install a newer version of texdoc in
	TEXMFHOME.
	- Rework print_config_files() to allow for the new 'disabled' status.
	- Remove 'abc/../' components from paths before using or displaying
	them.
	- Make the search functions case-insensitive on all platforms.
	- Include the output of -f, as well as the 'arg[0]' and version, in the
	output of 'debug1'.
	- Rename noise_level to verbosity_level, -n to -v and -v to -V.
	- Complain about unkown options in configuration files.
	- New verbosity level 5 (debug2): print each affectation to the config
	table with the origin of the value.

	* texdoc.cnf: Use the new last_file_switch directive.

